main event: An unidentified object was observed descending rapidly in the NW sky in St. Paul, Minnesota, on January 30, 1962.
interesting points: The object was seen by many individuals from various vantage points,The observation lasted for approximately 5 minutes,The object was described as having no distinctive characteristics, and was not considered a threat to national security, The observer reported a belief that it could have been a large meteor resulting in a shock wave, The object moved at a high speed and changed angles during its descent.
witness description: Witness testimonies from various individuals with airborne or ground vantage points
